.IX Title "HWRF::WPP 3"
.TH HWRF::WPP 3 "2015-09-02" "perl v5.10.1" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.\" For nroff, turn off justification.  Always turn off hyphenation; it makes
.\" way too many mistakes in technical documents.
.if n .ad l
.nh
.SH "NAME"
HWRF::WPP \- Perl extensions for the HWRF Testing and Evaluation suite.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 4
\&  use HWRF::WPP;
\&  my $wpp = HWRF::WPP\->new();
\&  $wpp\->source();
\&  $wpp\->compile();
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
The \fB\s-1HWRF::WPP\s0\fR module provides Perl functions that are commonly used in
building and running.
.PP
It is a \fBHWRF::Component\fR, all methods exported by are provided for
this package too.
.SS "\s-1EXPORT\s0"
.IX Subsection "EXPORT"
None by default.
.SS "\s-1METHODS\s0"
.IX Subsection "METHODS"
\fInew\fR
.IX Subsection "new"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        my $wpp = HWRF::WPP\->new();
.Ve
.PP
Instantiates an \s-1HWRF::WPP\s0 object.
.PP
\fIupdate_conf\fR
.IX Subsection "update_conf"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $c\->update_conf();
.Ve
.PP
The function \fBupdate_conf\fR will patch the configuration file adding the
debugging options to the C and Fortran compiler flags.
.PP
\fIpatch_config\fR
.IX Subsection "patch_config"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $c\->patch_config(file => "arch/Config_new.pl");
.Ve
.PP
The function \fBpatch_config\fR will patch the file \fIarch/Config.pl\fR
unless the option \fIfile\fR is specified. It will
.IP "Change all occurrences of \fBatm_pom\fR to \fBatm_ocn\fR" 4
.IX Item "Change all occurrences of atm_pom to atm_ocn"
.PD 0
.IP "Add on the first blank line in the file: select((select(\s-1STDOUT\s0), $|=1)[0]);" 4
.IX Item "Add on the first blank line in the file: select((select(STDOUT), $|=1)[0]);"
.PD
.PP
This is to make \s-1STDOUT\s0 hot, so that perl flushes it whenever
data is written, even if it is not attached to a tty.
.PP
\fI\fR
.IX Subsection ""
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $c\->patch();
.Ve
.PP
The function \fBpatch\fR will apply any package/compiler/site specific patches
needed before compiling the module.
.PP
In the case of \s-1WPP\s0, this adds \fI\-ftz\fR to the \fI\s-1FFLAGS\s0\fR when using the
Intel compiler. This prevents float point exceptions in the w3 library,
namely lib/w3lib/getbit.f:65
	\s-1NINT\s0(G(I1)*S)/S
